What are some reasons why people enjoy playing board games? Can you provide some examples using JSON data? 
{
  "game1": {
    "name": "Monopoly",
    "description": "A classic game of property trading and management",
    "appeal": ["strategic thinking", "friendly competition"],
    "benefits": ["spending time with friends/family", "improving math and money management skills"]
  },
  "game2": {
    "name": "Catan",
    "description": "A game of resource management and settlement building",
    "appeal": ["collaborative gameplay", "endless replayability"],
    "benefits": ["socializing with others", "developing negotiation and decision-making skills"]
  },
  "game3": {
    "name": "Codenames",
    "description": "A word game of guessing and deduction",
    "appeal": ["teamwork and communication", "quick and easy to learn"],
    "benefits": ["improving language skills and vocabulary", "boosting creativity and critical thinking abilities"]
  }
}

Board games offer a variety of reasons for enjoyment, ranging from social interaction to cognitive challenges. Here's a JSON representation that outlines some of the reasons why people enjoy playing specific board games:

